obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (37139)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758&sectionId=37139&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Police-Forces`
  line `(Restriction of Rights) Act, 1966.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such ^1date as may be appointed in this behalf by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) in a ^2Union territory, by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) in a ^3State by the Government of that State:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed by the Central Government for different`
  line `Union territories.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 3rd December, 1966, vide notification No. G.S.R. 1848, dated 3rd December, 1966, in respect of the Union territory of Delhi,`
  line `see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `2. 1st August, 1967, vide notification No. S.O. 1122(E), dated 20th July, 1967, in respect of the Union territories of Andaman`
  line `and Nicobar Islands, Chandigarh, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `3. 4th September, 1967, vide Panjab Govt. notification No. S.O. 67 C. A. 33/66/S. 1/67, dated 2nd, September, 1967, in respect`
  line `of the State of Panjab, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (37140)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758&sectionId=37140&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "member of a police-force" means any person appointed or enrolled under any enactment`
  line `specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) "police-force" includes any force charged with the maintenance of public order;`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (37141)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Restrictions respecting right to form association, freedom of speech, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758&sectionId=37141&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No member of a`
  line `police-force shall, without the express sanction of the Central Government or of the`
  line `prescribed authority,—`
  line
  line `(a) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any trade union, labour union, political`
  line `association or with any class of trade unions, labour unions or political associations; or`
  line
  line `(b) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any other society, institution, association or`
  line `organisation that is not recognised as part of the force of which he is a member or is not of a purely`
  line `social, recreational or religious nature; or`
  line
  line `(c) communicate with the press or publish or cause to be published any book, letter or other`
  line `document except where such communication or publication is in the bona fide discharge of his duties`
  line `or is of a purely literary, artistic or scientific character or is of a prescribed nature.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—If any question arises as to whether any society, institution, association or organisation`
  line `is of a purely social, recreational or religious nature under clause (b) of this sub-section, the decision of`
  line `the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) No member of a police-force shall participate in, or address, any meeting or take part in any`
  line `demonstration organised by any body of persons for any political purposes or for such other purposes as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (37142)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758&sectionId=37142&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Any person who contravenes the provisions of section 3 shall, without prejudice to any`
  line `other action that may be taken against him, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (37143)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to amend Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758&sectionId=37143&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, amend the Schedule by including therein any other enactment relating to a force charged with the`
  line `maintenance of public order or by omitting there from any enactment already specified therein and on the`
  line `publication of the notification such enactment shall be deemed to be specified in, or as the case may be,`
  line `omitted from, the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament, as soon as may be, after it is issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (37144)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758&sectionId=37144&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00017_196633_1517807324758
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days, which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or ^1`
  line `[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid] both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
